WEBVTT

00:40.457 --> 00:43.418
ALL CHARACTERS, PLACES, GROUPS, AND
ORGANIZATIONS IN THIS WORK ARE FICTITIOUS

00:43.501 --> 00:46.379
SCENES WITH ANIMALS ARE STAGED
ACCORDING TO ANIMAL WELFARE GUIDELINES

00:47.297 --> 00:50.091
20 YEARS AGO

00:50.175 --> 00:52.552
SEON-A BILLIARD CLUB

01:03.938 --> 01:04.939
Dad?

01:05.899 --> 01:10.445
SEON-A BILLIARD CLUB

01:11.654 --> 01:12.739
Seon-a.

01:15.950 --> 01:18.369
Seon-a, where are you?

01:29.172 --> 01:31.216
Ahn Seon-a.

01:31.299 --> 01:32.801
Why are you lying here?

01:32.884 --> 01:36.387
Seon-a, wake up. Wake up now.

01:36.471 --> 01:38.431
I told you to wake up!

01:39.557 --> 01:40.600
Wake up.

01:43.686 --> 01:45.021
She must have been exhausted.

01:45.104 --> 01:46.272
-Let's go home.
-Seon-a.

01:46.356 --> 01:47.899
-You'll be okay after some rest.
-Seon-a.

01:47.982 --> 01:50.485
-You can't do this. Please stop.
-My baby.

01:50.568 --> 01:51.736
Wake up, Seon-a.

01:51.820 --> 01:53.154
You can't be doing this.

01:53.238 --> 01:55.490
-She's just really exhausted!
-Please.

01:55.573 --> 01:57.575
Wake up, Ahn Seon-a!

01:59.202 --> 02:01.454
You should have been there!

02:02.914 --> 02:04.666
Why would you leave your sister alone?

02:04.749 --> 02:06.084
Why?

02:07.585 --> 02:10.338
Why did it have to be Seon-a and not you?

02:14.884 --> 02:15.969
Hey, kid.

02:19.013 --> 02:20.723
Are you Ahn Seon-a's little brother?

02:23.643 --> 02:25.520
I heard you were the one who found her.

02:26.312 --> 02:27.897
Did you see anything strange?

02:36.865 --> 02:39.951
Was your sister alone in the billiard club
when you went out to play?

02:42.120 --> 02:43.121
Hey.

02:43.705 --> 02:44.998
Answer me!

02:45.081 --> 02:46.249
Hey.

02:47.292 --> 02:49.168
Why would you shout at a kid?

02:51.963 --> 02:52.797
Goodness.

02:53.339 --> 02:54.465
We're sorry.

02:55.717 --> 02:56.593
Hey.

02:57.260 --> 02:59.762
I heard your sister was
a well-known prodigy.

03:01.347 --> 03:03.099
Then you must be smart as well.

03:06.311 --> 03:08.021
You must like yo-yos.

03:08.104 --> 03:10.106
My son is always playing with them too.

03:12.108 --> 03:13.526
It's okay. You can keep playing with it.

03:22.535 --> 03:24.913
Do you want me to take you
to your mom and dad?

03:29.876 --> 03:31.461
All right. Let's go.

03:34.297 --> 03:35.465
Mister.

03:41.846 --> 03:44.098
-Come out this way.
-Please move.

03:44.182 --> 03:45.725
Why are you doing this?

03:45.808 --> 03:47.685
Honey.

03:48.228 --> 03:50.146
Why are you taking him?

03:50.230 --> 03:51.147
Honey.

03:51.231 --> 03:52.815
This can't be happening.

03:53.399 --> 03:54.442
Honey.

03:55.235 --> 03:56.236
Honey.

03:56.736 --> 03:58.988
Why is this happening?
I can't believe this.

03:59.572 --> 04:01.950
Honey.

04:09.832 --> 04:13.503
A mathematically gifted young girl
who gained popularity on a quiz show

04:13.586 --> 04:16.339
was found in a billiard club,
strangled to death.

04:16.422 --> 04:19.342
This is now known
as the Math Prodigy Murder Case.

04:19.926 --> 04:21.469
Shockingly, the culprit was found to be

04:21.552 --> 04:25.056
-the victim's father, Ahn.
-Goodness. I feel so bad for them.

04:25.139 --> 04:27.934
That father is nothing but a beast.

04:28.643 --> 04:30.561
How can he kill
his own daughter like that?

04:32.105 --> 04:33.731
Lower your voice.

04:34.315 --> 04:35.149
ANGOK SUPERMARKET

04:35.233 --> 04:37.360
-Do you want that?
-Yes.

04:39.195 --> 04:40.321
Thanks.

04:41.364 --> 04:42.615
Dae-bum.

04:42.699 --> 04:45.660
-Take this home.
-It's okay.

04:48.454 --> 04:50.248
I heard he told the police.

04:50.331 --> 04:52.458
Watch your words in front of the kid.

04:53.001 --> 04:54.210
SEON-A BILLIARD CLUB

04:55.378 --> 04:56.963
Mom, I'm home.

04:58.548 --> 04:59.590
Mom?

05:07.598 --> 05:09.267
Mom, I'm home.

05:11.185 --> 05:12.353
Mom.

05:13.646 --> 05:14.939
Mom!

05:36.044 --> 05:39.088
"About what happened last time…"

05:40.339 --> 05:41.424
That's not it.

05:45.094 --> 05:49.640
I'M SORRY, MR. LIBRARIAN
I DON'T KNOW HOW TO SAY THIS, BUT…

05:55.354 --> 05:58.274
I FOUND OUT LATER…

06:03.946 --> 06:05.490
Stop it.

06:10.495 --> 06:11.829
Stop disturbing me.

06:11.913 --> 06:12.872
I need to write this.

06:14.957 --> 06:16.125
Gosh, you.

06:16.709 --> 06:17.752
Fine.

06:17.835 --> 06:19.837
Let's go.

06:19.921 --> 06:21.964
Come here!

06:30.056 --> 06:30.932
Hey.

06:31.015 --> 06:32.975
-Come to school today, okay?
-What?

06:33.059 --> 06:34.936
I'm your older sister, you know.

06:35.019 --> 06:37.730
Why do you care if I go to school or not?

06:37.814 --> 06:40.358
I keep getting called up
to the office because of you.

06:40.942 --> 06:42.944
They want us to come in with a guardian.

06:43.027 --> 06:44.946
-You'll get held back if you don't…
-Ha-neul.

06:45.738 --> 06:46.781
Ha-neul.

06:48.741 --> 06:50.535
Take this.

06:51.119 --> 06:52.620
I heard you need it by this week.

06:53.287 --> 06:55.456
It's fine.
I don't need to go on the field trip.

06:55.540 --> 06:58.000
What do you mean? Take it with you.

06:58.084 --> 07:00.002
-Wait.
-Give it here.

07:00.086 --> 07:02.922
No, don't take that. It's for Ha-neul.

07:03.005 --> 07:04.423
He said he doesn't need it.

07:04.507 --> 07:06.175
What a piece of trash.

07:07.426 --> 07:08.594
Goodness.

07:08.678 --> 07:10.388
-I'll see you later, Grandma.
-Okay.

07:46.757 --> 07:47.925
I'm sorry.

07:56.726 --> 07:58.853
THE BATHROOM IS OUTSIDE

08:06.027 --> 08:06.861
I'M SORRY

08:27.131 --> 08:30.009
Hey, Bom.
Are you coming to the library today?

08:30.092 --> 08:31.802
I brought ice cream.

08:38.893 --> 08:40.978
Sorry, Yeo-reum. I'm at school right now.

08:41.771 --> 08:43.731
My bad. I won't bother you then.

08:45.149 --> 08:46.150
Excuse me.

08:46.234 --> 08:49.070
Thank you for the flowers.

08:49.153 --> 08:51.030
ANGOK PUBLIC LIBRARY

08:51.781 --> 08:52.823
You're welcome.

08:58.371 --> 09:00.623
You must have heard about Jun.

09:03.251 --> 09:04.293
Yes.

09:06.295 --> 09:07.338
I'm sorry.

09:07.838 --> 09:11.092
Not at all.
It was my fault for not telling you.

09:16.722 --> 09:17.807
Then I'll…

09:18.516 --> 09:20.726
I'll take good care of the flowers.

09:21.477 --> 09:22.436
Sure.

09:29.318 --> 09:30.361
Mr. Librarian.

09:35.866 --> 09:37.535
Do you want some ice cream?

09:52.300 --> 09:53.426
You know,

09:54.468 --> 09:57.263
I prefer cone ice creams over popsicles.

09:59.640 --> 10:01.017
What about you?

10:02.101 --> 10:05.563
I'm not a big…
Well, ice cream does taste good,

10:07.231 --> 10:10.359
-but the apple flavor…
-You don't have to answer me.

10:12.945 --> 10:14.822
But this one is good.

10:14.905 --> 10:16.115
Okay.

10:19.827 --> 10:22.997
I actually decided to live here

10:23.080 --> 10:26.500
because I fell in love with this library.

10:27.251 --> 10:28.294
I see.

10:30.880 --> 10:32.798
You've actually told me that already.

10:34.592 --> 10:35.760
I have?

10:36.552 --> 10:37.595
Yes.

10:38.679 --> 10:39.805
When?

10:41.140 --> 10:42.224
Back then…

10:44.769 --> 10:45.895
Back then.

10:47.480 --> 10:48.522
Back…

10:49.607 --> 10:50.608
then?

10:55.821 --> 10:57.698
What else did I say?

10:58.866 --> 11:02.536
It wasn't so much talking,
but rather singing.

11:03.954 --> 11:05.122
I sang?

11:06.999 --> 11:07.958
Sang?

11:09.418 --> 11:11.003
I sang?

11:11.087 --> 11:12.380
What did I sing?

11:16.717 --> 11:17.760
Why…

11:19.929 --> 11:20.846
That song.

11:22.431 --> 11:24.517
Why do you appear before my eyes

11:24.600 --> 11:26.394
Whenever I'm drunk

11:26.477 --> 11:28.270
Stop. Can you please stop that?

11:30.356 --> 11:33.150
Can you please forget
about that entire night?

11:34.193 --> 11:36.946
-Well, it's not like…
-I'll do anything to help you forget.

11:37.947 --> 11:40.783
I don't really think about it that--

11:40.866 --> 11:43.452
Come on, you even sang the song.

11:43.536 --> 11:44.870
That's because you asked.

11:46.247 --> 11:47.540
So embarrassing.

11:49.041 --> 11:50.084
Hey, Kim Bom.

11:50.668 --> 11:51.752
How come you came to school?

11:51.836 --> 11:54.088
Don't act like you know me at school.

11:54.630 --> 11:56.257
Are you going to the library today?

11:56.340 --> 11:58.175
I told you to get lost.

11:58.259 --> 12:00.386
-This is awesome.
-What the hell?

12:00.469 --> 12:01.554
Damn it.

12:02.138 --> 12:04.014
-Damn it.
-Kim Bom!

12:04.098 --> 12:05.224
Long time no see.

12:05.891 --> 12:07.560
That little bitch has no manners.

12:09.645 --> 12:10.896
Darn it.

12:11.480 --> 12:13.607
Something smells like
a fucking slut in here.

12:13.691 --> 12:15.693
I guess some slut came to school.

12:15.776 --> 12:17.403
-Right?
-Should we do some cleaning?

12:17.486 --> 12:19.196
-Why don't we?
-Come on.

12:20.573 --> 12:21.657
Kim Bom.

12:22.158 --> 12:23.909
Come out while we're still being nice.

12:23.993 --> 12:25.536
We're not done with you.

12:26.203 --> 12:28.789
I told you to come out, you fucking whore.

12:29.331 --> 12:30.958
So fucking annoying.

12:35.796 --> 12:37.006
-Gosh!
-Nice!

12:38.382 --> 12:39.216
That's awesome.

12:41.260 --> 12:42.219
Ma'am.

12:42.303 --> 12:43.971
Something's going down
in the bathroom. Hurry.

12:44.054 --> 12:46.140
-Hey!
-You're dead if I see you again.

12:46.223 --> 12:47.725
What are you guys doing here?

12:47.808 --> 12:48.976
Let's go.

12:56.025 --> 12:57.026
Hey, Kim Bom.

12:57.526 --> 12:59.487
Why can't you stay out of trouble?

12:59.570 --> 13:00.821
Hey, Bom.

13:00.905 --> 13:03.115
-Are you okay?
-Heo Jae-hun!

13:03.199 --> 13:04.366
Come see me.

13:10.831 --> 13:12.791
Did you skip school to hang out with her?

13:13.542 --> 13:15.085
-No.
-Stop lying.

13:16.462 --> 13:18.881
Don't hang out
with a girl like that, okay?

13:20.216 --> 13:21.550
Why aren't you answering?

13:23.177 --> 13:25.179
You coming back here from the US

13:25.262 --> 13:27.723
-is embarrassing enough for your parents--
-Auntie.

13:28.349 --> 13:30.351
I'm going to call your parents then.

13:31.060 --> 13:32.102
Sorry.

13:33.646 --> 13:36.232
So you better behave yourself, okay?

13:44.782 --> 13:46.992
Gosh, who do they all think they are?

13:47.493 --> 13:48.869
They act so high and mighty.

13:49.453 --> 13:50.829
They won't do it?

13:55.209 --> 13:56.126
I mean,

13:56.794 --> 13:59.922
I guess it's not easy to come down here
to listen to old people talk.

14:02.383 --> 14:04.009
That's not the issue here.

14:04.718 --> 14:06.595
They might make me write it.

14:08.180 --> 14:09.765
I don't even write a diary.

14:09.848 --> 14:12.977
Gosh, I have to do it tomorrow.
What do I do?

14:13.060 --> 14:14.311
Isn't there anyone else?

14:19.275 --> 14:23.946
I only proofread when I was working
at the publishing company.

14:24.029 --> 14:27.241
It's completely different
from writing from scratch.

14:27.324 --> 14:30.286
The fact that you proofread
means you're familiar with writing.

14:30.369 --> 14:32.162
I heard you majored in literature too.

14:32.246 --> 14:33.581
You're much better than us.

14:33.664 --> 14:35.165
Please, Yeo-reum.

14:35.249 --> 14:36.417
But still…

14:36.500 --> 14:38.210
Please. It's just for this month.

14:38.294 --> 14:40.170
Just help me out this once.

14:40.254 --> 14:42.548
I'm just not very confident…

14:42.631 --> 14:45.301
It's worse for me.
I don't even write a diary.

14:46.051 --> 14:46.969
Ms. Lee.

14:50.014 --> 14:53.183
Why do you appear before my eyes

14:55.060 --> 14:56.186
What did you say?

14:58.355 --> 14:59.481
Who appeared?

14:59.565 --> 15:00.566
It's nothing.

15:12.411 --> 15:14.330
Did I bring any lipstick?

15:16.540 --> 15:17.499
Let's see.

15:18.375 --> 15:19.919
I'm sure I brought at least one.

15:24.173 --> 15:25.883
What am I doing?

15:37.728 --> 15:38.979
Maybe it's there.

16:02.461 --> 16:04.296
Is this too much?

16:04.380 --> 16:05.547
Ms. Lee.

16:10.678 --> 16:11.720
Hello.

16:12.221 --> 16:13.389
Hello.

16:25.067 --> 16:26.568
Shall we go then?

16:27.945 --> 16:28.862
Okay.

16:32.741 --> 16:33.784
Hey, Bom.

16:34.535 --> 16:35.494
Hey.

16:40.040 --> 16:41.625
Are you still upset?

16:42.793 --> 16:44.003
Sorry.

16:44.086 --> 16:46.088
I won't act like I know you at school.

16:48.048 --> 16:48.966
Hey, Bom.

16:49.842 --> 16:50.968
Listen.

16:52.511 --> 16:53.595
I'm sorry.

16:54.722 --> 16:56.265
Please forgive me.

16:58.017 --> 16:59.601
I should have known.

17:03.772 --> 17:05.315
You did nothing wrong.

17:06.442 --> 17:08.777
I was just too embarrassed.

17:11.739 --> 17:12.740
Bom!

17:16.869 --> 17:17.911
What?

17:19.204 --> 17:20.914
What's with that face?

17:22.332 --> 17:24.543
-Whatever. Just come and carry this.
-Okay.

17:27.671 --> 17:29.339
-Should I carry your bag too?
-No.

17:29.423 --> 17:31.383
-Isn't it heavy?
-It's not.

17:31.467 --> 17:32.801
-It's heavy.
-I said no.

17:32.885 --> 17:34.303
I'll carry it for you.

17:37.890 --> 17:38.849
Hello.

17:38.932 --> 17:40.225
Hello.

17:42.603 --> 17:45.773
We're here for an interview.

17:50.944 --> 17:51.904
Ma'am.

18:09.755 --> 18:11.548
You can sit here.

18:13.467 --> 18:14.551
Goodness.

18:16.553 --> 18:18.055
You're dressed so nicely.

18:21.183 --> 18:23.268
Just relax,

18:23.811 --> 18:27.606
and imagine that
you're having a chat with your daughter.

18:34.780 --> 18:35.989
Thank you.

18:38.909 --> 18:40.452
-Thank you.
-It's hot.

18:42.830 --> 18:43.914
What's your name?

18:44.498 --> 18:45.624
Why is that important?

18:45.707 --> 18:46.917
Just do the interview.

18:50.712 --> 18:52.005
Go on.

18:56.677 --> 18:58.011
That's…

18:58.095 --> 19:00.305
You need to add sugar
to make it delicious.

19:00.389 --> 19:01.348
Here.

19:02.766 --> 19:03.767
Give this to him.

19:10.440 --> 19:11.358
Eat.

19:13.026 --> 19:16.572
Then may I ask how old you are?

19:16.655 --> 19:18.699
Age doesn't matter when you're this old.

19:22.786 --> 19:23.787
Goodness.

19:24.788 --> 19:27.457
I see so many flies flying around
all of a sudden.

19:51.440 --> 19:53.025
My kids are all grown up.

19:53.108 --> 19:56.987
My grandchildren just started walking.
They're so adorable.

19:57.070 --> 20:02.659
They're the apple of my eye.
Words cannot explain how cute they are.

20:02.743 --> 20:05.871
I still remember
how they toddled in through that door

20:05.954 --> 20:08.081
calling for their grandmother.

20:08.165 --> 20:09.583
-They are so adorable.
-Ma'am.

20:09.666 --> 20:11.293
-Well…
-But my grandkids,

20:11.376 --> 20:13.003
-they don't really--
-Ma'am.

20:13.086 --> 20:15.923
-What?
-May I go to the bathroom real quick?

20:16.006 --> 20:18.217
Sure. The bathroom is over there.

20:18.300 --> 20:19.843
-Over there.
-Thank you.

20:19.927 --> 20:22.429
I knew this would happen.
You drank a lot of water.

20:22.512 --> 20:26.141
Why didn't she finish this? What a waste.

20:30.103 --> 20:31.897
Gosh, it's so bitter!

20:31.980 --> 20:34.358
You've been eating this the whole time?

20:34.441 --> 20:36.944
Are you stupid or what?
You should have said something.

20:37.027 --> 20:38.237
Gosh, that startled me.

20:38.320 --> 20:40.781
Why didn't you say anything?

21:05.389 --> 21:07.266
Gosh, I'm so sorry.

21:07.808 --> 21:11.728
I had no idea I was sprinkling salt
instead of sugar.

21:12.688 --> 21:13.647
The bathroom…

21:14.690 --> 21:16.608
You have to tell me these things.

21:16.692 --> 21:18.151
Goodness.

21:18.235 --> 21:20.946
What is your husband doing?

21:21.029 --> 21:22.114
My husband?

21:22.781 --> 21:25.409
My husband passed away.

21:25.492 --> 21:28.078
What would he be doing up there?
There's nothing to do.

21:28.161 --> 21:30.163
He's probably just lazing around.

21:31.540 --> 21:35.335
It would be great
if he could watch over us from above.

21:36.128 --> 21:37.921
But it's so strange.

21:38.422 --> 21:41.174
We weren't so nice to each other
when he was alive,

21:41.883 --> 21:44.261
but now I miss him from time to time.

21:44.344 --> 21:46.847
I hurt my leg two years ago,

21:46.930 --> 21:49.975
so I used to go to a hospital in Seoul
to get treatment.

21:50.058 --> 21:52.436
But even though I went to the hospital,

21:52.519 --> 21:56.690
but that didn't help much.
I'm still limping around.

22:00.110 --> 22:02.487
GRADE 7 PUBLIC SERVANTS
WRITTEN EXAM RESULTS

22:04.698 --> 22:06.491
ACCEPTED APPLICANTS

22:07.075 --> 22:08.618
It was eight, five, three, seven.

22:09.536 --> 22:10.787
Eight, five, three, seven…

22:10.871 --> 22:11.872
five, eight, four…

22:14.916 --> 22:16.918
Eight, five, three,
seven, five, eight, four…

22:28.013 --> 22:29.222
No way.

22:31.183 --> 22:32.142
Goodness.

22:36.396 --> 22:39.066
I had no idea it was time for food.

22:39.149 --> 22:40.233
You guys must be hungry.

22:40.734 --> 22:41.568
Help yourselves.

22:41.651 --> 22:44.613
-Let's eat together, ma'am.
-I don't need to eat.

22:45.447 --> 22:47.157
-Thank you for the food.
-Sure.

22:50.535 --> 22:51.703
This is so delicious.

22:51.787 --> 22:52.954
-Really?
-Yes.

22:53.038 --> 22:54.372
Is it not salty?

22:56.416 --> 22:58.585
My name is Kim Bong-sun.

22:58.668 --> 23:01.046
And I'm 75 years old.

23:01.630 --> 23:04.091
But I'm registered as 72 years old.

23:04.674 --> 23:06.301
You look healthy.

23:06.384 --> 23:08.178
Indeed. I am healthy.

23:09.179 --> 23:11.389
Are you two married?

23:13.475 --> 23:15.519
No. We're not.

23:15.602 --> 23:17.687
We're not married.

23:20.857 --> 23:23.693
You guys would make a great couple
if you were to marry.

23:33.578 --> 23:37.374
While I was on my way here,
I felt burdened.

23:38.375 --> 23:41.545
All I did was listen to her stories,

23:42.212 --> 23:43.755
but my heart is at ease now.

23:45.257 --> 23:46.383
I'm glad to hear that.

23:48.927 --> 23:51.763
You fixed the lights for her, didn't you?

23:51.847 --> 23:52.848
Yes.

23:56.268 --> 23:58.061
You're like Santa Claus.

24:01.273 --> 24:02.315
Ms. Lee.

24:04.192 --> 24:07.863
May I ask if you can keep
working with me on this?

24:09.239 --> 24:10.323
But I…

24:11.533 --> 24:15.787
You won't like my writing
once you get to read it.

24:21.334 --> 24:22.419
Okay.

24:23.461 --> 24:26.423
If you buy me dinner, I'll think about it.

24:30.343 --> 24:31.761
You mean today?

24:32.304 --> 24:33.930
But we just ate.

24:36.183 --> 24:38.476
I think I'll get hungry
with all this walking.

24:49.613 --> 24:52.073
I'm sorry to keep you waiting.

24:52.157 --> 24:54.242
No problem. Time flies when you read.

24:54.743 --> 24:57.704
Why don't you wipe
that drool off your face first?

24:57.787 --> 24:58.747
Yeo-reum.

24:58.830 --> 25:02.083
This is fermented kimchi from Grandma.
You can make some stew with it.

25:02.667 --> 25:05.378
I couldn't buy kimchi
because it was so expensive.

25:05.462 --> 25:06.796
What? Kimchi is expensive?

25:06.880 --> 25:08.673
All we have at home is kimchi.

25:09.466 --> 25:10.634
Ms. Lee.

25:11.301 --> 25:13.970
Shall we go to dinner?

25:15.263 --> 25:17.682
What? Is he buying us dinner?

25:17.766 --> 25:19.184
I'm in. What about you?

25:20.352 --> 25:22.646
Gosh, you're so quick
when it comes to food.

25:22.729 --> 25:24.898
Thank you. I was starting to get hungry.

25:25.482 --> 25:26.316
Dae-bum.

25:26.399 --> 25:27.817
-Dae-bum.
-Hey.

25:27.901 --> 25:29.736
-What do I do?
-What's wrong?

25:29.819 --> 25:30.987
I passed.

25:38.286 --> 25:39.955
-Congratulations.
-Thank you.

25:40.038 --> 25:41.706
They announced the results today.

25:41.790 --> 25:43.875
After you went out in the morning,

25:43.959 --> 25:46.419
I was torn about whether I should
check it alone or with you.

25:46.503 --> 25:48.338
-But I checked it. And I passed!
-Hey!

25:49.130 --> 25:52.550
You called everyone in the neighborhood!

25:52.634 --> 25:55.595
Dong-cheol called and asked me
if you really passed the exam.

25:55.679 --> 25:57.138
No way. I didn't call him.

25:57.222 --> 25:58.348
Whatever.

25:58.431 --> 26:02.352
In any case,
this calls for a celebration dinner!

26:02.435 --> 26:03.395
Are you buying?

26:03.478 --> 26:04.938
No, Ms. Cho Ji-yeong is.

26:05.021 --> 26:07.941
Chang-su! This is great news.

26:08.024 --> 26:09.109
I brought company.

26:09.192 --> 26:11.820
-Ms. Cho, what brings you here?
-Hello.

26:11.903 --> 26:14.531
Ms. Cho Ji-yeong became
a grade seven public servant today.

26:14.614 --> 26:15.824
-Really?
-What do we call her now?

26:15.907 --> 26:18.451
-Stop it.
-Gosh. Congratulations.

26:18.535 --> 26:19.452
Thank you.

26:19.536 --> 26:21.579
-Come and help.
-Bring the tables together.

26:21.663 --> 26:23.999
-Let's go.
-All right.

26:24.082 --> 26:25.375
Gosh, this is great.

26:25.458 --> 26:26.918
-Hello.
-Let me clean the table.

26:27.002 --> 26:28.503
-Sit here.
-Thank you.

26:28.586 --> 26:31.589
JEIL RESTAURANT

26:31.673 --> 26:33.550
Hey, it's mustard leaf kimchi.

26:34.134 --> 26:36.052
I brought some lettuce for wraps.

26:36.136 --> 26:38.138
Can we eat them here?

26:38.680 --> 26:40.932
Lettuce? Where did you get them?

26:41.016 --> 26:42.017
Let me see.

26:42.100 --> 26:45.186
We went to interview an old lady today,

26:45.270 --> 26:47.022
and she gave us lettuce.

26:47.105 --> 26:48.565
What interview?

26:48.648 --> 26:51.818
A writer didn't show up,
so Yeo-reum did the interview instead.

26:51.901 --> 26:54.821
How did you know how to do that?
Where did you work in Seoul?

26:54.904 --> 26:56.781
-She worked at a publishing company.
-I see.

26:56.865 --> 26:58.992
Then you must have
had a lot of boyfriends.

27:00.285 --> 27:03.663
How are those two relevant?

27:03.747 --> 27:07.125
I've always found well-read girls
charming and attractive.

27:07.208 --> 27:09.419
So? Do you have a boyfriend?

27:10.670 --> 27:11.504
I…

27:13.131 --> 27:15.383
I used to have one, but we broke up.

27:16.760 --> 27:18.303
Why? How long did it last?

27:23.224 --> 27:24.809
-Quite a long--
-Ji-yeong.

27:24.893 --> 27:26.561
This is about to burn. You should eat it.

27:26.644 --> 27:27.896
-Okay.
-Hurry and eat.

27:28.605 --> 27:30.023
-Thank you.
-It's hot.

27:31.858 --> 27:34.903
Gosh, Dae-bum. You don't even know
how to grill meat properly.

27:34.986 --> 27:37.072
You have to season it with salt like this.

27:37.155 --> 27:38.740
Why would you season it with salt?

27:38.823 --> 27:40.700
-Salt makes the meat richer.
-Whatever.

27:40.784 --> 27:41.868
You ruined it.

27:42.952 --> 27:44.079
What is that on your shirt?

27:44.162 --> 27:46.706
I heard the exam
is extremely difficult to pass.

27:46.790 --> 27:48.666
-It is.
-Tell me about it.

27:49.167 --> 27:52.253
She's never been smart,
but she's always been a hard worker.

27:52.337 --> 27:53.755
Gosh, seriously?

27:53.838 --> 27:57.092
I mean, your grades were worse than mine
back in middle school.

27:57.175 --> 27:59.427
-Damn it.
-What? Worse than you?

27:59.511 --> 28:00.762
Yes. That's right.

28:00.845 --> 28:03.848
She devoted herself to studying
after she did worse than me.

28:03.932 --> 28:05.892
That's why she went to university.

28:05.975 --> 28:10.063
And she had to take the lowest exam
five times before she barely passed.

28:10.146 --> 28:14.442
In Angok, she's the best of the best
when it comes to putting in the effort.

28:17.612 --> 28:18.947
Go on.

28:19.030 --> 28:21.199
So back then, I gave her a nickname.

28:21.282 --> 28:23.493
Chew Ji-yeong, for chewing up her exams.

28:23.576 --> 28:25.161
-Stop it already.
-Fine.

28:25.787 --> 28:28.289
This seems like a good time to step out.
Have fun.

28:28.373 --> 28:31.000
But I heard that even trying takes talent.

28:31.584 --> 28:32.794
Talent, my foot.

28:33.503 --> 28:36.548
Those who are truly talented
don't even try hard for these things.

28:37.465 --> 28:38.633
What about you, Bom?

28:39.217 --> 28:40.969
You're always drawing in the library.

28:42.387 --> 28:45.473
Hey, this is great.
I've always wanted to tell you something.

28:46.182 --> 28:47.642
Coming from my life experience,

28:48.226 --> 28:52.939
if you make up excuses
and put off what you really want to do,

28:53.690 --> 28:55.608
you'll regret it.

28:55.692 --> 28:57.569
You're already in your junior year.

28:57.652 --> 29:01.030
If you really like drawing,
use that to go to a university,

29:01.614 --> 29:03.825
rather than wasting your stop doodling.

29:04.451 --> 29:07.078
Why are you patronizing me
when you don't even know?

29:07.162 --> 29:09.205
Aren't we here to have dinner?

29:10.415 --> 29:12.834
Bom. I'm just saying this
because I feel bad for you.

29:13.585 --> 29:16.004
Look. Life is all about timing.

29:16.087 --> 29:17.297
You don't think so, right?

29:17.881 --> 29:19.340
-I made a wrap for you.
-Dae-bum can't relate

29:19.424 --> 29:20.800
because he's special.

29:21.843 --> 29:25.388
Normal people like us have to
try as hard as we can.

29:25.472 --> 29:28.141
We have to be ready
to seize an opportunity when it's time.

29:29.267 --> 29:30.894
If you lose your chance,

29:30.977 --> 29:32.437
then it's over.

29:33.688 --> 29:34.898
I'm serious.

29:35.982 --> 29:41.488
But I don't think everyone has
a solid purpose in their life.

29:42.113 --> 29:43.698
Because I don't either.

29:46.201 --> 29:47.368
I see.

29:49.829 --> 29:50.914
But…

29:52.248 --> 29:56.336
isn't that why you settled here
to recreate yourself

29:56.419 --> 29:57.879
and plan your future?

29:57.962 --> 30:01.424
Not really.
I just try to have a good time.

30:03.468 --> 30:06.888
Why don't we start
having a good time now, Ji-yeong?

30:07.472 --> 30:09.098
Eat some wraps,

30:09.182 --> 30:11.643
-some meat…
-Dae-bum.

30:12.185 --> 30:14.813
Why do you keep cutting me off?

30:16.856 --> 30:18.191
I just wanted you to eat.

30:18.900 --> 30:23.446
From what I heard,
everything Ms. Cho said is right.

30:23.530 --> 30:27.158
Bom. You must become a proper adult
for your family to live.

30:29.160 --> 30:30.787
What a crappy evening.

30:30.870 --> 30:32.664
Listen with an open heart.

30:32.747 --> 30:35.583
How long do you think
your grandma could support you?

30:36.167 --> 30:37.377
I always say this,

30:37.460 --> 30:40.463
but your dad will never overcome
his addiction to liquor.

30:40.547 --> 30:41.923
-So you should--
-Hey.

30:42.507 --> 30:44.342
Can you please watch what you say?

30:44.425 --> 30:46.469
What's with that tone?

30:46.553 --> 30:49.722
How can the owner kick a customer out
with her words?

30:50.306 --> 30:53.852
And you should be thanking Yeo-reum
for holding me back.

30:55.395 --> 30:58.648
And by the way, you should give Yeo-reum
back her 450,000 won.

30:58.731 --> 31:01.276
-You little brat.
-Hey, wait for me.

31:01.359 --> 31:05.321
Congratulations, congratulations

31:05.405 --> 31:09.075
Congratulations to Ji-yeong
for passing the exam

31:09.158 --> 31:10.201
Hey, where's everyone?

31:12.120 --> 31:13.288
Blow it out.

31:15.999 --> 31:17.292
Gosh, my head hurts.

31:18.585 --> 31:19.961
What's with the air in this room?

31:21.296 --> 31:22.672
Hey, blow it already.

31:23.840 --> 31:25.091
I even got seven candles.

31:28.803 --> 31:30.138
All right, everyone.

31:30.221 --> 31:32.432
For another round,
how about we go to karaoke

31:32.515 --> 31:34.183
to liven up the mood?

31:34.976 --> 31:37.186
Actually, I have to get going.

31:37.270 --> 31:38.229
What?

31:38.771 --> 31:41.524
I'll be going home as well, Ji-yeong.

31:42.108 --> 31:43.651
Seong-man can go by himself then.

31:43.735 --> 31:45.737
What do you mean? What's with you guys?

31:45.820 --> 31:46.779
Yeo-reum.

31:46.863 --> 31:48.281
I'll give you a ride.

31:48.364 --> 31:49.991
It's okay. I can walk home.

31:50.074 --> 31:52.493
Look at all this.
How will you walk with these?

31:52.577 --> 31:55.121
-Hey, Ji-yeong. Are you really going?
-Yes.

31:55.204 --> 31:57.540
We should hang out when we can
on days like this.

31:57.624 --> 31:59.584
I even asked my dad
if I can stay out late.

31:59.667 --> 32:02.211
Then you should.
No one is stopping you from hanging out.

32:02.295 --> 32:03.838
Enjoy yourself, okay?

32:03.922 --> 32:05.048
Hey, I mean…

32:05.673 --> 32:06.966
Goodbye, Ji-yeong.

32:07.050 --> 32:08.426
-Goodbye.
-Goodbye.

32:11.596 --> 32:13.264
Drive safely.

32:16.851 --> 32:17.894
Gosh.

32:20.855 --> 32:22.398
What do we do now?

32:29.572 --> 32:31.199
As Seong-min said,

32:31.282 --> 32:33.451
it'd be a shame to go home early.

32:33.534 --> 32:34.911
Do you want to grab some beer?

32:35.745 --> 32:36.871
Right now?

32:37.538 --> 32:39.332
There's a good sashimi place I like.

32:39.415 --> 32:40.959
I don't take just anyone there.

32:42.919 --> 32:45.004
But I'm a little full.

32:45.088 --> 32:46.381
Just have a little.

32:46.464 --> 32:47.674
Okay?

32:51.177 --> 32:53.262
-Dae-bum. By the way…
-Yes?

32:53.346 --> 32:57.350
Do you know if Ji-yeong plans to leave
right away now that she's passed the exam?

32:57.433 --> 33:00.728
She needs to do an interview,
and she might blow that.

33:00.812 --> 33:04.649
But this interview is more of a formality,
so she'll get in.

33:05.400 --> 33:06.484
Oh, really?

33:08.528 --> 33:11.197
She's finally going to
make it to Seoul then.

33:12.198 --> 33:13.366
-Seong-min.
-Yes?

33:14.951 --> 33:16.369
You must be bittersweet.

33:16.452 --> 33:17.537
Me?

33:18.246 --> 33:20.665
Why would I be? I feel relieved.

33:21.457 --> 33:23.584
I'll even send the interviewers gifts,

33:23.668 --> 33:25.253
to beg them to give her a pass.

33:25.878 --> 33:27.922
The issue is not me, but you.

33:28.006 --> 33:30.800
Ji-yeong was the only one
you spoke comfortably to.

33:30.883 --> 33:34.554
More people die from loneliness
than starvation these days.

33:34.637 --> 33:36.180
You should go out and meet someone.

33:36.806 --> 33:38.599
You're wasting your handsome looks.

33:39.142 --> 33:41.102
Don't just laugh.

33:41.811 --> 33:43.813
Do you want me to introduce you to a girl?

33:45.106 --> 33:46.107
You?

33:46.774 --> 33:47.984
"You"?

33:48.067 --> 33:50.778
Do you think I'm a loner?
I have lots of gal pals.

33:51.362 --> 33:52.655
Tell me your ideal type.

33:52.739 --> 33:54.240
Cute types? Sexy types?

33:54.323 --> 33:55.742
I don't have a preference.

33:55.825 --> 33:58.536
-There must be a celebrity you like.
-Goodness.

33:58.619 --> 34:00.329
-Did you just say IU?
-What?

34:00.913 --> 34:02.623
If you want to meet IU, follow me.

34:02.707 --> 34:04.542
Seong-min. I'll really get going now.

34:04.625 --> 34:06.377
You wanted IU. Hurry up and follow me.

34:09.547 --> 34:12.050
-Congratulations on passing the exam.
-Thank you.

34:12.133 --> 34:14.510
I heard grade seven exams are difficult.

34:15.887 --> 34:17.722
It took blood, sweat, and tears.

34:18.431 --> 34:22.143
And I couldn't have passed it
without Dae-bum's help.

34:22.226 --> 34:23.311
Mr. Librarian?

34:23.811 --> 34:26.230
It's hard to see
what an extraordinary person he is

34:26.314 --> 34:27.899
from just meeting him.

34:30.860 --> 34:35.198
Dae-bum got accepted to
Korea National University when he was 17.

34:35.281 --> 34:36.866
He was the youngest researcher.

34:38.242 --> 34:39.410
Fascinating, right?

34:39.952 --> 34:44.040
He's too competent to be here
working for a countryside library.

34:45.625 --> 34:47.210
I can't tell you more,

34:48.377 --> 34:49.670
but he's been through a lot.

34:52.715 --> 34:56.677
When people treat him badly in ignorance,

34:56.761 --> 34:58.721
I get so frustrated.

34:58.805 --> 35:00.848
Even the kids who come to the library.

35:00.932 --> 35:04.352
Jun and his friends.
They don't respect him.

35:04.936 --> 35:06.562
They need to be scolded.

35:07.688 --> 35:09.607
You must care about him a lot.

35:10.983 --> 35:11.818
Well…

35:13.027 --> 35:15.029
We've spent a long time together.

35:18.324 --> 35:22.161
But it seems like he's gotten
comfortable around you.

35:23.454 --> 35:24.580
Maybe.

35:27.500 --> 35:29.335
I'm happy that I passed the exam,

35:30.920 --> 35:34.340
but I'm worried about
Dae-bum being here alone without me.

35:38.719 --> 35:40.471
-So annoying.
-Damn it.

35:41.430 --> 35:42.515
Who the fuck is this?

35:45.143 --> 35:46.394
It's Kim Bom.

35:47.186 --> 35:48.980
Where do you think you're going, bitch?

35:50.648 --> 35:52.275
You should greet your seniors.

35:53.151 --> 35:54.861
You don't even come to school.

35:54.944 --> 35:56.821
Why the fuck are you wearing this?

35:57.405 --> 35:59.323
Do you get paid more to fuck
with the uniform on?

36:00.199 --> 36:01.909
Seriously.

36:01.993 --> 36:03.494
Is that all you bitches can think about?

36:03.995 --> 36:05.371
Gosh, you're so scary.

36:06.122 --> 36:07.582
Too bad.

36:07.665 --> 36:10.793
Your bodyguard, Dae-ho, is behind bars.

36:11.586 --> 36:12.753
Hey.

36:12.837 --> 36:15.089
You guys are nothing when you're alone.

36:15.173 --> 36:17.508
Do you feel like you're worth more
when you're grouped up like this?

36:17.592 --> 36:19.135
So fucking pathetic.

36:19.886 --> 36:21.137
-Move.
-Where are you going?

36:21.721 --> 36:23.389
Are you off to make money
for your dad's liquor?

36:23.931 --> 36:25.474
You guys know too, right?

36:25.558 --> 36:27.226
Her dad is a piece of shit.

36:27.768 --> 36:29.562
I heard her mom used to work at a bar.

36:30.146 --> 36:32.940
And she's the product
of them getting drunk together.

36:33.024 --> 36:34.650
-So fucking disgusting.
-So retarded.

36:34.734 --> 36:37.236
-What a slut.
-Why won't anyone stop talking today?

36:37.320 --> 36:38.362
-Hey!
-Hey!

36:38.446 --> 36:41.199
-Let go!
-Come here!

36:45.286 --> 36:47.205
Yeo-reum, hop in. I'll take you home.

36:47.288 --> 36:49.123
-It's okay. I can walk home.
-No.

36:49.207 --> 36:50.750
It's too far. It's not safe.

36:50.833 --> 36:52.084
Just wait a bit.

36:56.672 --> 36:59.550
You know, there's something
I really want to ask you.

37:00.927 --> 37:04.096
Don't you feel anxious
about not doing anything?

37:09.435 --> 37:10.478
I do.

37:10.978 --> 37:13.064
You do, right?

37:13.648 --> 37:16.108
What if Bom takes after you?

37:16.192 --> 37:19.779
You're a grown-up.
You're free to think relaxing is cool.

37:19.862 --> 37:21.614
But she's still a kid.

37:21.697 --> 37:24.492
What I'm saying is you can ruin her life.

37:25.409 --> 37:26.994
Don't you feel anxious?

37:27.703 --> 37:30.539
Why would I feel anxious?
I work in the public sector.

37:36.128 --> 37:37.505
Actually,

37:40.174 --> 37:43.302
I broke down trying to live up
to other people's standards.

37:45.680 --> 37:48.391
I was troubled because
I thought everyone was running ahead

37:48.474 --> 37:50.893
while I was the only one falling behind.

37:54.772 --> 37:56.023
So for now…

37:57.024 --> 38:01.195
I'm trying to become friends with myself
rather than others.

38:01.696 --> 38:02.780
I see.

38:04.824 --> 38:07.618
I have no idea what you're saying.
My head hurts.

38:08.119 --> 38:09.537
Also,

38:10.371 --> 38:13.207
I haven't known Mr. Librarian
for a long time,

38:14.500 --> 38:15.751
but he's warm-hearted.

38:16.877 --> 38:20.923
The kids like him
because they can feel his kindness.

38:21.674 --> 38:23.384
It's not that they take him for a fool.

38:25.553 --> 38:27.179
So don't worry.

38:27.263 --> 38:29.348
I'm sure he'll be okay on his own.

38:36.522 --> 38:37.481
Hello?

38:38.065 --> 38:40.693
I'm at Bangrim Seafood.

38:40.776 --> 38:42.820
Can you come to pick me up? I drank a bit.

38:42.903 --> 38:45.031
Sorry, thanks. Bye, I'll wait.

38:46.866 --> 38:48.451
-I'll get going then.
-No.

38:48.534 --> 38:50.411
He'll be here soon. Just wait a bit.

38:50.494 --> 38:52.705
It's fine. I just want to sober up.

38:53.998 --> 38:55.458
Take care.

38:56.417 --> 38:58.127
Goodbye, then.

39:02.298 --> 39:03.382
Bye.

39:16.270 --> 39:17.480
Why did I say that?

39:21.192 --> 39:23.027
It's not like I know anything.

39:34.497 --> 39:35.956
Hi, Bom.

39:38.042 --> 39:39.210
What happened?

39:39.877 --> 39:40.961
Bom.

39:41.670 --> 39:42.713
Bom!

39:44.090 --> 39:45.883
What happened to my baby's face?

39:45.966 --> 39:48.511
I tripped on my way home. It's nothing.

39:49.303 --> 39:51.055
How can they be so harsh?

39:51.138 --> 39:53.849
How can they beat up
a small girl like you?

39:54.433 --> 39:57.061
Nothing like that happened.
I honestly just tripped.

39:57.144 --> 40:00.147
Let's go inside.
Let me put some ointment on you.

40:00.231 --> 40:02.566
-Grandma, I told you it's nothing.
-Goodness.

40:03.067 --> 40:04.235
Hey, you brat.

40:05.236 --> 40:08.030
Look how messy you are.

40:08.531 --> 40:11.200
How dare you go around picking fights?

40:11.283 --> 40:12.576
Just close the door.

40:14.120 --> 40:17.623
That little bitch takes after her mom.

40:18.124 --> 40:20.084
How could you say that to her?

40:20.584 --> 40:21.752
Close the door.

40:22.378 --> 40:24.046
It's your fault.

40:24.130 --> 40:26.632
What? What did you say?

40:27.633 --> 40:29.593
This is all your fault.

40:29.677 --> 40:32.096
You're why Mom ran away
and why we live like this.

40:32.179 --> 40:34.098
It's all your fault!

40:34.181 --> 40:35.850
What did you say, you fucking bitch?

40:35.933 --> 40:37.268
Why did you even have me?

40:37.351 --> 40:38.477
Why?

40:38.561 --> 40:40.104
Just die!

40:40.187 --> 40:42.481
Bom, why are you acting like this?

40:42.565 --> 40:44.358
Fine! Let's die!

40:45.359 --> 40:46.819
We can all die together!

40:46.902 --> 40:49.196
How can you call yourself a dad?

40:49.280 --> 40:50.656
Just die!

40:50.739 --> 40:52.032
Bom.

40:52.116 --> 40:53.784
-Bom!
-Fine!

40:53.868 --> 40:56.871
Leave just like your mom did, you bitch!

40:57.788 --> 41:00.291
Just fucking die!

41:00.374 --> 41:01.876
You fucking brats!

41:06.088 --> 41:07.131
Ji-yeong.

41:07.214 --> 41:08.966
Am I going to be your lackey forever?

41:09.800 --> 41:12.761
Just think of this as a gift
to congratulate me.

41:12.845 --> 41:16.182
Gosh. You and your selfishness.

41:17.475 --> 41:18.601
I'm sleepy.

41:20.060 --> 41:21.103
Hey.

41:22.062 --> 41:23.230
And…

41:24.857 --> 41:26.525
Drop me off at Dae-bum's.

41:27.318 --> 41:28.402
What?

41:29.153 --> 41:31.655
Why would you go to his house
at this hour?

41:32.281 --> 41:34.408
I have something to discuss with Dae-bum.

41:34.950 --> 41:36.076
Do it when it's bright.

41:36.160 --> 41:39.580
Do you think it's normal for you
to visit a man's house at this hour?

41:39.663 --> 41:41.457
People will spread rumors about you.

41:42.124 --> 41:43.834
That's what I'm hoping for.

41:43.918 --> 41:44.793
What?

41:45.503 --> 41:46.420
Look at you.

41:46.504 --> 41:49.089
Have you done something like this before?

41:49.173 --> 41:50.674
Yes. I'm going to sleep now.

41:50.758 --> 41:52.092
-What?
-Wake me up later.

41:52.718 --> 41:54.845
-Did you just say "yes"?
-Good night.

41:56.013 --> 41:58.724
This is driving me nuts. I mean…

41:59.225 --> 42:00.476
Damn.

42:11.529 --> 42:12.655
Hey, we're here.

42:14.240 --> 42:15.491
Hey, thanks.

42:17.868 --> 42:19.036
Goodbye.

42:21.789 --> 42:23.040
Hey, Ji-yeong.

42:24.250 --> 42:26.710
I also have something to tell Dae-bum,

42:26.794 --> 42:27.795
so let's go together.

42:27.878 --> 42:29.296
Tell him what?

42:29.380 --> 42:30.297
Tell him later.

42:30.381 --> 42:33.050
Wait, Ji-yeong.

42:33.133 --> 42:35.010
Don't forget your cake.

42:35.094 --> 42:36.679
Eat it with Jun.

42:36.762 --> 42:38.639
No. I can't have cake.

42:38.722 --> 42:40.349
I'm nauseous right now. Just take it.

42:40.432 --> 42:42.142
Actually, if you could
leave me two pieces,

42:42.226 --> 42:43.352
that would be perfect.

42:43.435 --> 42:44.895
-Bye.
-Hey.

42:45.479 --> 42:47.022
Are you really going in there?

42:47.606 --> 42:48.691
Answer me!

42:50.859 --> 42:52.027
Goodness.

42:52.111 --> 42:54.572
You're terrible. Seriously.

42:59.660 --> 43:00.619
Ji-yeong.

43:05.207 --> 43:06.917
What brings you here at this hour?

43:08.377 --> 43:09.461
Tell me.

43:10.254 --> 43:12.298
Look at you.

43:13.507 --> 43:14.883
You seem different.

43:15.843 --> 43:18.512
Did you drink a lot?

43:19.305 --> 43:20.723
Of course, I did.

43:20.806 --> 43:22.558
-Gosh.
-Sit down.

43:24.602 --> 43:27.605
Why did you drink until so late?

43:29.189 --> 43:30.899
I was chatting with Yeo-reum.

43:31.650 --> 43:33.193
She's an interesting one.

43:33.777 --> 43:34.987
You were…

43:36.280 --> 43:38.115
drinking with Yeo-reum?

43:42.870 --> 43:46.707
Today is such a wonderful day for me.

43:48.083 --> 43:49.752
So can you do me a favor?

43:51.420 --> 43:52.504
What is it?

43:54.173 --> 43:55.799
You have to promise me first.

43:56.592 --> 43:59.428
Well, tell me what it is first.

44:01.138 --> 44:02.181
Do you

44:02.765 --> 44:06.226
want to meet him after hearing about it?

44:06.310 --> 44:09.063
Or do you want to meet him
without knowing?

44:10.022 --> 44:12.483
Are you talking about the professor?

44:14.109 --> 44:15.569
You're so smart.

44:16.779 --> 44:18.822
He's coming here to see you tomorrow.

44:20.449 --> 44:21.492
Hey.

44:21.575 --> 44:23.285
He's an admirable professor.

44:23.369 --> 44:26.372
He's coming all this way
to meet a disrespectful student like you.

44:26.455 --> 44:29.792
So don't think about
running away somewhere.

44:29.875 --> 44:33.462
I'll have my eyes wide open
to keep you right here.

44:34.129 --> 44:35.255
Okay?

44:38.759 --> 44:40.511
And let's go to Seoul together.

44:44.515 --> 44:45.683
Come with me.

44:53.482 --> 44:54.650
Hey, Bom.

44:55.776 --> 44:56.735
Yeo-reum.

44:58.445 --> 44:59.696
Are you okay?

45:00.406 --> 45:02.116
I had nowhere to go.

45:07.913 --> 45:09.039
You came to the right place.

45:10.082 --> 45:12.084
Gosh, that looks painful.

45:25.556 --> 45:26.640
It hurts, right?

45:27.224 --> 45:28.350
It's okay.

45:29.268 --> 45:30.352
You must be exhausted.

45:31.019 --> 45:31.854
Get some sleep.

45:32.646 --> 45:33.647
Hey.

45:35.107 --> 45:37.526
Yeo-reum. Aren't you…

45:38.318 --> 45:40.487
Aren't you going to ask what happened?

45:42.990 --> 45:44.575
Do you want to talk about it?

45:48.078 --> 45:48.996
No.

45:51.707 --> 45:54.835
Tell me when you're ready.

45:56.712 --> 45:57.963
But Bom.

46:00.215 --> 46:02.468
I don't know what's going on,

46:04.845 --> 46:06.180
but don't get yourself hurt.

46:14.605 --> 46:15.856
I'm turning off the lights.

46:37.711 --> 46:38.754
Good night.

46:40.255 --> 46:41.882
You too.

47:15.457 --> 47:18.961
Think of this as your second home
and come over whenever you want to.

47:19.044 --> 47:21.255
Thanks to you, I feel happier now.

47:21.838 --> 47:23.715
She's having surgery in that room.

47:23.799 --> 47:26.343
How did you get injured?

47:26.426 --> 47:28.095
Dad might go to prison for this.

47:28.178 --> 47:30.681
Let's say I hurt her.
I'll go to prison instead.

47:30.764 --> 47:31.765
Ma'am.

47:31.848 --> 47:33.016
The hospital bill is 10 million won.

47:33.100 --> 47:36.270
I was wondering
if I could get the rent money back.

47:36.353 --> 47:38.063
Is this about Bom's hospital bill?

47:38.146 --> 47:40.941
Could you take care of Gyeo-ul?

47:41.525 --> 47:42.776
I liked it here.

47:43.277 --> 47:46.405
Subtitle translation by: Jea-Heon Chung
